Heat olive oil in a large saucepan over medium heat. Add fennel seeds and garlic; cook 1 minute, stirring frequently. Add tomato juice, and bring to a boil. Reduce heat, and simmer 2 minutes. Remove from heat; stir in basil, hot pepper sauce, and teaspoon salt. Place soup in a large bowl; cover and chill 6 hours or overnight. Strain mixture through a sieve over a bowl; discard solids. Stir in zucchini and next 5 ingredients. Spoon 1 cup into each of 6 shallow bowls; top each serving with 1 teaspoon sour cream and green onions, if desired. Serve immediately.